e` 的处理上，而非网络传输。\n\n### 结论\n调用链数据支持\"adservice是根因\"的假设，因为：\n- `adservice` 的延迟显著增加（10 倍）。\n- 延迟增加是最下游的，且影响了上游服务。\n- 其他服务的延迟增加可能是由于 `adservice` 的瓶颈。\n\n### 输出\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\"rrt_max\", \"frontend->adservice\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"adservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Normal median: 5556.67, Fault median: 54704.85 (10x increase)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```", "log_analysis_findings": "基于获取到的日志数据，我现在可以分析根因假设。从日志中可以看出，这是一个明确的Byteman故障注入测试场景。\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_log_keys\": [\"Byteman\", \"stress\", \"AdService--stress-1749640247\", \"StressHelper\", \"java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException\", \"Agent failed to start\", \"Rule.execute\", \"thread\", \"Transformer\", \"trigger\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"adservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"Byteman stress injection testing targeting all three adservice instances with stress rules\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Installed rule using default helper : AdService--stress-1749640247, AdService--stress-1749640247 execute(), Rule.execute called for AdService--stress-1749640247, Creating thread AdService--stress-1749640247\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**分析依据：**\n\n1. **明确的Byteman故障注入证据**：日志显示在所有三个adservice实例（adservice-0、adservice-1、adservice-2）上都执行了相同的Byteman stress规则 `AdService--stress-1749640247`\n\n2. **stress规则执行**：日志中出现大量 `AdService--stress-1749640247 execute()` 和 `Rule.execute called for AdService--stress-1749640247` 记录，表明stress规则正在持续执行\n\n3. **多线程stress测试**：日志显示创建了多个stress线程（如 `Creating thread AdService--stress-1749640247`），这解释了CPU使用率大幅上升的原因\n\n4. **协调一致的故障模式**：所有三个adservice实例都显示相同的故障注入行为，这与假设中描述的\"Byteman stress injection testing affecting all three instances\"完全一致\n\n5. **与之前的metric证据吻合**：日志中显示的stress注入与metric专家报告的adservice CPU使用率从0.01/0.0上升到0.6（200%增加）完全吻合\n\n因此，日志数据强烈支持\"adservice is the root cause due to Byteman stress injection testing affecting all three instances\"这一假设。", "metric_analysis_findings": "Based on the trace data analysis, I can now validate the hypothesis about adservice being the root cause due to Byteman stress injection testing. Let me analyze the evidence:\n\n**Key Findings Supporting the Hypothesis:**\n\n1. **Consistent CPU Usage Spike Across All Adservice Instances**: All three adservice pods (adservice-0, adservice-1, adservice-2) show identical CPU usage patterns:\n   - adservice-0: CPU increased by 193.44% (0.01 → 0.6)\n   - adservice-1: CPU increased by 200% (0.0 → 0.6)  \n   - adservice-2: CPU increased by 200% (0.0 → 0.6)\n\n2. **Significant Latency Degradation in Adservice**: \n   - adservice-0: rrt increased by 149.72%, rrt_max increased by 128.65%\n   - adservice-1: rrt increased by 72.46%, rrt_max increased by 75.55%\n   - adservice-2: rrt increased by 77.75%, rrt_max increased by 77.12%\n\n3. **Cascade Effects on Downstream Services**: The adservice issues propagated to other services:\n   - cartservice-0: rrt_max increased by 11.84%, p99 increased by 163.59%\n   - frontend services: significant rrt_max increases across all instances\n   - Other services show minor to moderate latency increases\n\n**Analysis Against the Hypothesis:**\n\nThe evidence strongly supports the hypothesis for several reasons:\n- The coordinated, identical CPU spike across all three adservice instances is characteristic of systematic stress injection\n- The timing and pattern match Byteman fault injection behavior\n- The cascade effects on downstream services are consistent with adservice being the primary bottleneck\n- No other service shows the same systematic, coordinated degradation pattern\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\"pod_cpu_usage\", \"rrt\", \"rrt_max\", \"memory_usage\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"adservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"All three adservice instances show coordinated pod_cpu_usage spikes (193-200% increase) and significant